cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing and its application in data annotation.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses supervised learning methods and co-training to improve the accuracy of distant supervision.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses text descriptions and lexicons for data annotation.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is mentioned in the abstract as an example of a real-world application that requires automated data annotation.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that encompasses many of the topics discussed in the paper, such as machine learning and natural language processing.
